---

### 10. Key Files Summary

**Critical Files to Understand:**

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `/packages/shadcn/src/registry/schema.ts` | Zod schemas that validate all registry items |
| `/apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/registry.ts` | Combines all registry item arrays into single registry |
| `/apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/ui/_registry.ts` | Registry entries for UI components |
| `/apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/examples/_registry.ts` | Registry entries for example/demo components |
| `/apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/ui/accordion.tsx` | Actual component implementation |
| `/apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/examples/accordion-example.tsx` | Demo/example implementation |
| `/apps/v4/public/r/index.json` | Final generated public registry (JSON) |
| `/packages/shadcn/src/utils/registries.ts` | Utilities for registry management |

---

### 11. Pattern Summary

**Compound Components:**
- Export multiple sub-components from single file (e.g., `Accordion`, `AccordionItem`, `AccordionTrigger`, `AccordionContent`)
- Each wraps a Radix UI primitive with styled wrapper
- All exported individually for consumer composition

**Registry Structure:**
- TypeScript definitions in `_registry.ts` files
- Each component has entry with name, type, files array, and meta links
- Examples have separate entries with same pattern
- All arrays aggregated in main `registry.ts` into single Registry object

**File Organization:**
- Components: `/ui/component-name.tsx`
- Examples: `/examples/component-name-example.tsx`
- Registry: `/ui/_registry.ts` and `/examples/_registry.ts`
- Each "base" (radix, base) mirrors this structure

This is a sophisticated, well-organized system for managing component libraries with multiple UI bases, examples, and comprehensive metadata.

